description._content: Catalog #: 09_01631 Title: First Lieutenant Harry Haw Special Collection Photo Huron South Dakota Additional Information: Harry Haw (on left) with Roy Giard and a Curtiss JN-4D/ OX5 ""Jenny"" aircraft in Huron, South Dakota, 20 June 1921, Harry Haw served in the U.S. Army in the 514th Observation Squadron. He entered the U.S. Army in 1917 and became a First Lieutenant in 1930. He became a civilian Transport Pilot by 1930 and had logged 789 flying hours by 1934. he later became Principal of the Alice Birney school.
